0.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service)
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| summarize avg(duration)
0.title: AVG Response Time

1.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| summarize count()
1.title: Total Spans

10.query:
fetch logs
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter isNotNull(trace_id)
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
| fieldsAdd trace_id = toString(trace_id)
//| parse content, """("[!dt" LD "]")? LD:content""" // fixes ugly logs
| join [
  fetch spans
  | fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
  | filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
    AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
    AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
  | fieldsKeep trace.id | dedup trace.id | fieldsAdd trace.id = toString(trace.id)
], kind:inner, on:right[trace.id]==left[trace_id]
| fieldsKeep timestamp, log.level, k8s.namespace.name, service.version, content, dt.entity.service.name, trace_id
| summarize `Logs found`=count()
10.title: Logs generated

| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name

2.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| summarize avg(span.timing.cpu)
2.title: AVG CPU Time

3.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| fieldsAdd http.request.method = coalesce(http.request.method, http.method, rpc.protocol)
| fieldsAdd request.name = coalesce(http.route, span.name)
| fieldsAdd request.name = if(request.name == "POST" OR request.name == "GET", endpoint.name)
| filterOut isNull(request.name)
| summarize { `count`=count(), avg=avg(duration), p50=median(duration), p99=percentile(duration, 99) }
  , by: { request.name, http.request.method }
| sort count desc
3.title: Top Slow Requests

4.title: Failed Requests

5.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service)
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| fieldsAdd request.name = coalesce(http.route, span.name)
| fieldsAdd request.name = if(request.name == "POST" OR request.name == "GET", endpoint.name)
| filterOut isNull(request.name)
| makeTimeseries  {p99=percentile(duration, 95)}
  , by: {dt.entity.service.name }, bins:100
5.title: Response Time Pp99

7.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service)
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| fieldsAdd request.name = coalesce(http.route, span.name)
| fieldsAdd request.name = if(request.name == "POST" OR request.name == "GET", endpoint.name)
| filterOut isNull(request.name)
| makeTimeseries  {ResponseTime=avg(duration)}
  , by: {dt.entity.service.name}, bins:100

8.query:
fetch spans
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) AND  request.is_failed == true
AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
| filterOut contains(endpoint.name, "json")
| fieldsAdd request.name = coalesce(http.route, span.name)
| fieldsAdd request.name = if(request.name == "POST" OR request.name == "GET", endpoint.name)
| filterOut isNull(request.name)
| makeTimeseries  {count=count()}
  , by: {dt.entity.service.name}, bins:250, nonempty:true
| limit 20
8.title: Failed Requests Over Time

9.query:
fetch logs
| fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
| filter isNotNull(trace_id)
| filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
| fieldsAdd trace_id = toString(trace_id)
| parse content, """("[!dt" LD "]")? LD:content""" // fixes ugly logs
| join [
  fetch spans
  | fieldsAdd entityName(dt.entity.service) // adds dt.entity.service.name
  | filter in(dt.entity.service.name, $Service) 
    AND if($SessionID != "ALL", matchesValue(request_attribute.sessionID, $SessionID), else:true) 
    AND if($DeveloperName != "NONE", matchesValue(`http.request.header.x-developer`, $DeveloperName), else:true) 
  | fieldsKeep trace.id | dedup trace.id | fieldsAdd trace.id = toString(trace.id)
], kind:inner, on:right[trace.id]==left[trace_id]
| fieldsKeep timestamp, log.level, k8s.namespace.name, service.version, content, dt.entity.service.name, trace_id
9.title: Logs based on service, sessionId and DeveloperName. Only works on smaller data sets.

variables.input:
data record(sessionIDs = "ALL")
| append [
  fetch spans 
  | filter isNotNull(`request_attribute.sessionID`)
  | summarize sessionIDs = collectDistinct(`request_attribute.sessionID`)
  | expand sessionIDs
  | limit 500
]
